 for bestpractices and # Contact / Support Form

## Overview
Create a public and authenticated Contact / Support Form for Roam Resort that supports general questions and concierge-specific support requests. The form should capture user context, route submissions to the appropriate team (concierge vs. support), and trigger transactional email flows (e.g., inquiry confirmations, signup verification, concierge messages, payment links, receipts). The system must be resilient to null/undefined data, validate all inputs, and guard against runtime errors per the project’s safety rules. The UI must align with the premium, editorial aesthetic described in the visual style guidelines and be accessible, responsive, and secure.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A dual-path Contact / Support page accessible publicly and behind authentication. Guests can submit general inquiries; authenticated users can submit concierge-specific requests with richer context (stay preferences, dates, guest count, prior inquiry references). The page should also accommodate concierge staff workflows via admin/internal panels.

Goals:
- Provide a straightforward, elegant form for general questions and concierge requests.
- Collect sufficient context to triage inquiries (subject, message, relevant destination/listing, dates, guests, reference numbers).
- Distinguish between “General Support” vs “Concierge Request” to route appropriately.
- Trigger email confirmations to the submitter and notify internal teams.
- Link to Stripe-related payment flows when concierge requires payment actions; handle manual payment state reconciliation as needed.
- Maintain excellent UX: guided form steps, clear validation, friendly inline hints, and post-submission acknowledgement with next steps.

Connected features:
- Email Notifications & Templates: Transactional emails for signup verification, inquiry confirmations, concierge messages, payment links, and receipts.
- Admin/Concierge workflows: View, update status, add internal notes, export inquiries, and track payment states.
- Authentication: Public form with optional login requirement for concierge workflows; authenticated users provide profile data automatically.

UI guidance and visuals:
- A refined, luxury editorial look with large hero sections, editorial typography, generous spacing, and card-based content blocks.
- Primary CTA: “Request a Stay” or “Submit Inquiry” integrated into destination pages and headers.
- Consistent nav, responsive behavior, subtle hover effects, and micro-interactions that reflect the brand.

API integrations:
- Note: No external API integrations beyond transactional email service (SendGrid) and internal APIs for inquiries, authentication, and admin controls.

## Components to Build
- ContactFormPage
  - Props: user (current user object if authenticated), destinationContext (optional: destinationId, name, images), mode (general vs. concierge), onSubmit callback.
  - State: form fields (name, email, subject, message, inquiryReference, destinationId, dates, guests, wantsConcierge boolean, preferredContactMethod), validationState, submissionStatus, serverErrors.
  - UI: Hero header, instruction copy, form fields, inline validation, informative placeholders, accessibility labels, consent/terms (if needed), success acknowledgement component.
  - Behavior: Frontend validation, progressive disclosure for optional fields, dynamic categorization (General vs Concierge), detect authenticated user to prefill name/email.
  - Safety: Guard all array/object accesses; use data ?? [] defaults for lists; use Array.isArray checks for any iteration.

- EmailTemplatesService
  - Functions: sendSignupVerification(user), sendInquiryConfirmation(submission), sendConciergeMessage(submission, internalNote), sendPaymentLink(submission), sendReceipt(submission).
  - Integration: Hook into SendGrid (or chosen provider). Ensure null-safe payload construction and fallback behavior if data is missing.

- InquiriesAdminPanel (Admin/Concierge)
  - Views: Inquiry list, detail view, status dropdown, internal notes, CSV export.
  - Data access: Ensure protections for admin-only routes; guard against null results; return empty arrays safely.

- DestinationSelector (Reusable)
  - UI: Destination search, list, and quick select; show editorial content.
  - Data handling: Safely handle possibly missing destination data.

- ValidationLibrary
  - Centralized validators for: email pattern, required fields, date ranges (stay dates), numeric guests, string length limits, and reference formats.
  - Use defensive checks to avoid calling array/string methods on nullish values.

- FormField components
  - TextInput, TextArea, Select, DateInput, NumberInput
  - Accessibility: ARIA labels, proper labeling, error messaging, focus management.

- Loader/Status components
  - Global spinner, success banner, error toast.

- Route/Pages
  - Public route: /contact
  - Auth-protected sub-route for concierge: /admin/inquiries (and nested routes)
  - Destination page integration: “Request a Stay” action connects to ContactFormPage with context

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- UI Components and Pages
  - Build a responsive ContactFormPage with a two-column layout on desktop (context panel + form) and a single-column stack on mobile.
  - Form fields: 
    - Name (prefill from user profile if authenticated)
    - Email (prefill if authenticated)
    - Subject (select: General Question, Concierge Request, Payment Inquiry, etc.)
    - Message (textarea)
    - Destination (auto-suggest/select, optional)
    - Dates (check-in/check-out) (optional for general; required for concierge)
    - Guests (optional)
    - Inquiry Reference (optional)
    - Preferred Contact Method (email/phone) (optional)
  - Submission flow:
    - Client-side validation with rules:
      - name: required, max length
      - email: required for submit; valid email format
      - subject: required
      - message: required, min length
      - dates/guests: required if Concierge Request
    - Guard against null/undefined values before mapping/iterating
    - Use data ?? [] for any array results
    - On success: show acknowledgement with next steps and a link to view confirmation (if available)
    - On error: show user-friendly error, keep form state for correction
  - Accessibility: proper focus management, keyboard navigation, screen-reader friendly error messages
  - Styling: adhere to Visual Style with typography, color palette, card designs, and interactive states
  - Data flow: Submit to backend API endpoint via POST; disable form during submission; handle 429/500 gracefully
  - Networking: Validate API response shapes; guard against nullish response.data; use Array.isArray(response?.data) checks

- Email Notification Triggers
  - After successful submission, call EmailTemplatesService to send:
    - Inquiry confirmation to user
    - Concierge update to internal team if Concierge Request
  - Ensure idempotency and safe payload creation
  - Include unsubscribe or opt-out preferences as required by policy

- Data Handling & State
  - Use React useState with appropriate defaults: useState<string>(""), useState<number>(0), useState<T[]>([]) for arrays
  - For fetched lists (destination options, etc.), ensure safe defaults: const destinations = data ?? [] and then Array.isArray(destinations) ? destinations.map(...) : []
  - Validate and sanitize all fields before API submission
  - Destructure with defaults: const { subject = "", message = "", ...rest } = formState ?? {}

- Security
  - CSRF protection on form submission endpoints (server-side)
  - Rate limiting for submissions if needed
  - Server-side authorization checks for admin routes
  - Do not expose sensitive data in the frontend payload

### Backend
- API Endpoints
  - POST /api/inquiries
    - Body: { name, email, subject, message, destinationId, dates, guests, inquiryReference, isConcierge, userId }
    - Validation: required fields, types, and logical checks (dates in future, guests > 0)
    - Returns: { id, status, createdAt, submissionUrl? }
  - GET /api/inquiries (admin only)
  - GET /api/inquiries/:id
  - PATCH /api/inquiries/:id
    - Admin operations: status updates, internal notes
  - POST /api/email/send
    - Used by EmailTemplatesService to trigger emails (abstracted)
- Database Tables
  - inquiries
    - id (UUID)
    - user_id (FK, nullable)
    - name
    - email
    - subject
    - message
    - destination_id (FK, nullable)
    - start_date (DATE, nullable)
    - end_date (DATE, nullable)
    - guests (INTEGER, nullable)
    - inquiry_reference (VARCHAR, nullable)
    - is_concierge (BOOLEAN)
    - status (ENUM: New, Contacted, In Progress, Deposit Paid, Confirmed, Closed)
    - internal_notes (TEXT, nullable)
    - created_at, updated_at
  - inquiry_payments (optional, if linking Stripe)
    - id, inquiry_id, payment_state, stripe_session_id, url
- Validation
  - All server responses should be shaped consistently; guard against null/undefined returns using Array.isArray checks and data ?? [] equivalents

### Integration
- Frontend to Backend
  - /api/inquiries POST handled by backend; ensure response contains safe data
  - Use centralized error handling to map server errors to user-facing messages
- Email Service
  - Configure templates for:
    - Signup verification (if applicable)
    - Inquiry confirmation
    - Concierge messages
    - Payment links
    - Receipts
  - Include robust placeholders and data validation in templates
  - Ensure SendGrid (or chosen provider) integration uses safe payloads; guard against missing fields
- Admin/Concierge
  - Admin panel reads inquiries, updates status, adds internal notes, and can export CSV
  - Ensure exports use safe data shaping and guard against null results

## User Experience Flow
1. Guest lands on Contact / Support page or clicks “Request a Stay” on a destination page.
2. User decides General Question or Concierge Request (toggle/based on subject).
3. User fills required fields:
   - General: name, email, subject, message (destination/dates/guests optional)
   - Concierge: additional destination, dates, guests, reference, notes
4. If authenticated, fields like name/email auto-fill; allow edits if needed.
5. Client-side validation runs; errors are inline and descriptive.
6. User submits; UI shows loading state; form is disabled during submission.
7. Backend creates a new inquiry, returns ID; emails are queued/sent.
8. User sees submission acknowledgement with expected next steps and contact options.
9. Concierge/Admin staff can view, update status, add notes, and export data in Admin Panel.
10. When payment is requested, a Stripe payment link is sent via email; payment state is tracked by concierge staff.

## Technical Specifications
- Data Models: See above
  - inquiries table with fields for user, subject, message, destination, dates, guests, concierge flag, status, notes
- API Endpoints:
  - POST /api/inquiries
  - GET /api/inquiries
  - GET /api/inquiries/:id
  - PATCH /api/inquiries/:id
  - POST /api/email/send (internal)
- Security:
  - Public route protection for public form; admin/concierge routes protected by authentication and role-based access (Guest, Host, Concierge)
  - Validate user session, ensure only authorized roles access admin endpoints
- Validation:
  - Server-side validation: required fields, type checks, string length constraints, date logic
  - Client-side validation: immediate feedback; mirror server validation
  - Use optional chaining and nullish coalescing when handling API responses

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The contact form renders correctly on desktop and mobile with responsive layout and accessibility considerations.
- [ ] All form fields are validated on the client; invalid inputs display clear messages; submission is blocked until valid.
- [ ] Submitting a general inquiry and a concierge request both create an inquiry record in the backend with correct flags and statuses.
- [ ] After submission, an email confirmation is sent via SendGrid and the user receives a confirmation message in UI.
- [ ] Admin panel supports listing, filtering by status, viewing details, updating status, adding internal notes, and exporting to CSV.
- [ ] All arrays and potential null values are guarded (e.g., (data ?? []).map(...) and Array.isArray checks) and useState initializations are typed correctly.
- [ ] All API responses are validated to ensure response?.data is an array or mapped safely; no runtime crashes due to null/undefined.
